The error you are encountering is due to a duplicate object key in the `devcontainer.json` file. In this case, the "suggest" key is defined twice in the JSON object, which is not allowed.

To fix this error, you need to remove the duplicate key definition and put all its related properties under one "suggest" key.

In the provided code snippet, change the JSON to include all the properties under one "suggest" key:

```json .devcontainer/devcontainer.json (30-39)
                    "stickyScroll.enabled": true,
                    "guides.bracketPairs": true,
                    "bracketPairColorization.enabled": true,
                    "suggest": {
                        "snippetsPreventQuickSuggestions": false,
                        "insertMode": "replace"
                    }
```

After making these changes, the error should be resolved.

Here's a complete working example for the provided JSON code:

```json .devcontainer/devcontainer.json (26-41)
                "settings": {
                    "json.schemas": [
                        {
                            "fileMatch": [
                                "**/vsc-extension-devkit/**/*.code-workspace"
                            ],
                            "schema": "https://json.schemas.dev/devcontainer.json"
                        }
                    ],
                    "stickyScroll.enabled": true,
                    "guides.bracketPairs": true,
                    "bracketPairColorization.enabled": true,
                    "suggest": {
                        "snippetsPreventQuickSuggestions": false,
                        "insertMode": "replace"
                    }
                },
```

